               <msContents>
                  <summary>This papyrus contains a letter to Phanias, a secretary of the Harbor of Memphis, concerning business matters. The writer mentions some wine and plants which he put on board a ship for Phanias, and tells him to remind two other persons about a matter, apparently a payment due.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Location: Ann Arbor</note>
                     <note type="general">Pub. status: Verso; Recto contains the middle portion of column 54 of a declaration to the strategus of the Memphite nome of produce in arrears.</note>
                     <note type="related">-</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
