                        <condition>
                           <ab type="conservation">Broken off at the top and at the right. There are traces of five vertical folds: four (inward) folds from right to left enclosing the letter, followed by a fifth (outward) fold revealing the address. The whole letter was then folded at least twice horizontally, once in the middle of the address (about line 9 of the letter), and at least once more below line 17, where the papyrus broke, constituting the bottom of the present piece, after which at least another third of the letter was lost.</ab>
